The paper discusses a benchmark dataset for performing hypothesis-driven data analysis using deep networks, specifically deep learning. The dataset is composed of 35 fonts, each with 11,172 written syllables consisting of 19 initial consonants, 21 medial vowels, and 28 final consonants. The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised and supervised methods to analyze the learned representations. Based on this information, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
